    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Early modern devices used to mint coins from metal blanks. These consisted of a large screw carrying the die in a holder mounted at its lower end. The screw was operated by workers pulling the weighted end of a long horizontal bar, which descended with great force to hit the blank on the bottom die.</Note_Text>
